---
title: Tandoori Broccoli Steak (v) with Fruity Spiced Rice and Tomato Salsa
description: If you’ve never had a broccoli ‘steak’ it’s exactly what it sounds like: broccoli sliced lengthwise into steak-like portions, seasoned, and either grilled or roasted (we’ve roasted ours here) until tender on the inside and crispy on the outside. Chef Jesse’s special marinade is a delicious combination of yoghurt, tandoori masala spice mix, lime juice, and olive oil ,and works perfectly with the other flavours and textures in this dish. Served with turmeric spiced rice and a zingy tomato salsa, this is vegetarian food at its best.
